What is state lifting in react ?
-> When multiple components need the same (common) data, we move that data (state) to their parent component and pass it down to the 
children using props.That is called state lifting.
example - 

Step 1: Move state to the parent
---------------------------------------
function Parent() {
  const [count, setCount] = React.useState(0);

  return (
    <>
      <ChildA count={count} setCount={setCount} />
      <ChildB count={count} />
    </>
  );
}

Step 2: Use props in children
----------------------------------------------------------------------

function ChildA({ count, setCount }) {
  return <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>A: {count}</button>;
}

function ChildB({ count }) {
  return <div>B: {count}</div>;
}















