------------------------------------------
An interceptor is a function that runs:
✅ Before a request is sent (Request Interceptor)
✅ After a response is received (Response Interceptor)

It allows you to:-
 -> Attach auth tokens
 -> Handle errors globally
 -> Log requests/responses
 -> Redirect on 401 unauthorized


Interceptor in React is usually implemented using Axios interceptors. 
It allows us to intercept and modify API requests before they are sent and handle responses globally.
It is commonly used for attaching authentication tokens and handling global errors like 401 unauthorized.

"In React projects, we usually create a separate API configuration file like src/api/axios.js where we configure Axios interceptors. 
Then we export that Axios instance and use it across services or components so that authentication tokens and global error handling are applied to all API calls."


